76561198078010274,Recommended,252150,29773798,Posted: 7 February,all,HotelKatz,"Grimm is a 3d platformer that revisits fairy tales. First in the modern watered down state, then has you change them back to a state that resembled the tales written hundren of years eariler. As in back when they were darker, crueler, and.... dare I say... grimmer? True, it still takes pot shots at the stories and cracks jokes every so often, even during the latter state.But part of the charm is in the humor, even if it does get a little bit crass, rude, and vulgar. For crying out loud, the targeting reticle is Grimm urinating at the spot where he would jump at.Each chapter is about a dollar or so. There's coins of Grimm found in the stages. Collect all in a chapter (which is a few stages) and you'll unlock a model viewer. The model viewer has only buildings and breakable things to look at, but it does allow you to see the change between the stuff's Sugary-sweet version and the grim version. The difficulty of collecting the coins isn't that hard, just look aroudn the stage. I didn have a little bit of a problem looking for one coin in the final stage, but it turned out to be on top of a building.The music does fit the setting, both when in the light version and dark version. I'll admit, the music is simple, short and repeats, but it's not going to ruin anything. The grimm-ified singing skull does have a ear worm-worth song in my mind, though.I had some difficulty at first, getting used to a keyboard and mouse controls, back when I first played this. Precision jumping is a little difficult to get used to and a tad trying during the 'Run!' moments. but given time and patience, you can get used to it.Is this worth buying? It's a nice jaunt through stories we've all read, listened to, and watched for dozons of times when either we were younger, or were looking after a child. And let's face it, we've all made those rude nasty jokes about fairy tales at one point or another. I say at least try the first stage. It's free, after all.Fun fact : The little icon for Jack and the Bean Stalk in the 'choose a story' menu uses an earlier version of the Grimm-ified Jack. The little icon has a straw hat, but the grimm-ified version is designed to look more like a punk or something."
